Package com.telenav.kivakit.resource

Class Extension

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.resource.Extension
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.comparison.Matchable<ResourcePathed>, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, Comparable<Extension>
public class Extension extends Object implements com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.comparison.Matchable<ResourcePathed>, Comparable<Extension>
A FileName extension, such as ".txt" or ".jar".

Common extensions are provided as static constants. An extension can also be constructed with parseExtension(Listener listener, String), with or without a dot prefix: 

 parseExtension(".xyz");
 parseExtension("xyz");

Properties

  • name() - The extension as a string
  • codec() - The codec normally used for files with this extension, or the NullCodec if the file is not compressed

Matching

  • matcher() - A matcher that matches resources with this extension
  • ends(Resource) - True if the given resource has this extension
  • endsWith(Extension)

Tests

  • endsWith(Extension) - True if this (compound) extension ends with the given extension
  • isArchive() - True if this extensions indicates an archive
  • isExecutable() - True if this extension is normally executable

Functional Methods

  • gzipped() - This extension with ".gz" on the end
